// Per-clip manifest for the audio pipeline. Source files live alongside this manifest under
// small-arms/, ambient-machinery/, explosions/, voice-dead-lines/, etc. Run
// `gradlew :asset-pipeline:processAudio` to encode into mod/sounds/.
//
// Each entry:
//   id     — output filename (sans .ogg) and the Starsector sound-id you reference from sounds.json
//   source — path relative to this manifest (asset-pipeline/src/tool/resources/audio/)
//   kind   — "ui" | "positional" | "music"
//              ui         → stereo, for showCustomVisualDialog / non-positional playback
//              positional → mono, for in-world combat-engine spatialized sounds
//              music      → stereo, full-length tracks (use with playCustomMusic)
//   out    — subfolder under mod/sounds/ to write to (empty/omitted = mod/sounds/ root)
//
// Comments and trailing commas are tolerated. ffmpeg must be on PATH (or $FFMPEG set).
